1) Introduction:
1.1 Document Purpose:
The purpose of this document is to define the requirements for a software system responsible for processing credit card transactions. It specifies the system's objectives, features, functional and non-functional requirements, design limitations, and provides an initial schedule and budget.
1.2 Document Scope:
This document outlines the requirements for a credit card processing software system that enables secure and efficient handling of credit card transactions. The system should support functions such as authorization, authentication, integration with payment gateways, transaction logging, and fraud detection.

1.3 Overview:
The credit card processing software system serves as a comprehensive solution for businesses to securely and efficiently process credit card transactions. It leverages modern technology and complies with industry standards and regulations.

2) General Description:
The credit card processing software system offers businesses a secure and dependable platform for processing credit card transactions. It facilitates the authorization and authentication of transactions, seamless integration with payment gateways, transaction logging for auditing purposes, and robust fraud detection mechanisms.

3) Functional Requirements:
The functional requirements of the credit card processing software system include:

Credit card authorization and authentication
Integration with payment gateways
Transaction logging and auditing
Fraud detection and prevention mechanisms
Real-time transaction status updates
Reporting and analytics

4) Interface Requirements:
The credit card processing software system should seamlessly integrate with various payment gateways and financial institutions. It should provide intuitive interfaces for businesses to manage transactions, view reports, and configure settings.

5) Performance Requirements:
The credit card processing software system must efficiently handle a large number of concurrent transactions, ensuring quick response times and high availability. It should be scalable to accommodate increased transaction loads and maintain optimal performance.

6) Design Constraints:
The credit card processing software system must comply with industry standards and regulations, ensuring adherence to data security and privacy requirements. It should utilize secure encryption methods, follow PCI DSS guidelines, and implement robust authentication mechanisms.

7) Non-Functional Attributes:
The credit card processing software system should demonstrate reliability, security, and scalability. It should offer a user-friendly interface, be easily maintainable, and deliver excellent performance even during peak transaction periods.

8) Preliminary Schedule and Budget:
The estimated development timeframe for the credit card processing software system is 10 months, with a budget of $400,000. Regular monitoring of the schedule and budget will be conducted to ensure project progress and financial control.
